    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Sora: Video Generation as a World Simulator"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "OpenAI's Sora (February 2024) is the first publicly demonstrated system to generate photorealistic video clips up to 60 seconds long from a text prompt — including complex camera trajectories, multi-shot scenes, and physically plausible dynamics like fluid simulation and rigid body interactions. OpenAI's technical report frames it as a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "world simulator"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ": an implicit 3-D physics engine learned entirely from video data."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key Architectural Innovation: Native-Resolution Patchification"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Earlier video models required all training clips to be resized to a fixed resolution (e.g. 256×256). Sora uses a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "NaViT-style variable-length patchification"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ": each video is encoded by a 3-D VAE into a compressed latent, then divided into spatiotemporal patches of a fixed size (e.g. 2×2 spatial × 1 temporal). The patches become a sequence of tokens with "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "3-D Rotary Positional Embeddings"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (3-D RoPE) that encode height, width, and time independently. Because the sequence length varies per video but the token size is fixed, a single model trains on clips of any resolution, aspect ratio, and duration simultaneously — no resizing, no padding."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This is significant: a model that trains at native resolution learns the statistical structure of each resolution class rather than the artifacts introduced by downsampling. At inference time you can request any resolution and duration (up to the model's trained distribution) simply by changing the patchification parameters."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Sora vs Runway Gen-3 Alpha: architecture overview and feature comparison table"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Sora's Transformer Architecture"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Sora is a Diffusion Transformer (DiT) operating on spatiotemporal patch tokens. The core loop is:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "A 3-D VAE encodes the video into a compressed latent of shape (T', H', W', C)."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "The latent is patchified into a variable-length sequence of tokens with 3-D RoPE positions."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Text is encoded by a T5-XXL encoder (and optionally a CLIP image encoder for image-to-video) into cross-attention keys and values."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "N transformer blocks apply full 3-D self-attention (every video token attends to every other video token) and cross-attention to text."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "A linear head predicts the noise (or velocity) for DDPM/flow-matching denoising."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "The denoised latent is decoded by the 3-D VAE back to pixel frames."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The full 3-D self-attention — no decomposition into separate spatial + temporal heads — is the primary reason Sora's outputs maintain globally coherent scene structure and convincing physics over long clips. The cost is quadratic in token count, requiring very large compute clusters and careful memory management (FlashAttention-2, sequence parallelism across GPUs)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prompting Sora via the API"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "As of late 2024, Sora is accessible through ChatGPT Plus and Pro tiers. OpenAI provides a Python SDK for the video generation endpoint. The interface is straightforward — specify the prompt, size, and duration:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# pip install openai\nfrom openai import OpenAI\nimport urllib.request\n\nclient = OpenAI()  # reads OPENAI_API_KEY from environment\n\n# Submit a text-to-video generation job\nresponse = client.videos.generate(\n    model=\"sora\",\n    prompt=(\n        \"Aerial drone shot tracking a red hot air balloon drifting \"\n        \"over a patchwork of autumn farmland at golden hour, \"\n        \"cinematic depth of field, 4K\"\n    ),\n    size=\"1920x1080\",\n    quality=\"high\",         # \"low\" for faster/cheaper previews\n    n=1,\n)\n\n# The API returns a job ID; poll or use webhooks for completion\nprint(\"Video ID:\", response.data[0].id)\nprint(\"Status:\",   response.data[0].status)   # e.g. \"queued\", \"completed\"\n\n# When status == \"completed\", download the output\nvideo_url = response.data[0].url\nurllib.request.urlretrieve(video_url, \"sora_output.mp4\")\nprint(\"Saved sora_output.mp4\")"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Sora also accepts an image as a conditioning input (image-to-video) and can extend or vary existing video clips via the Storyboard feature, which lets users define keyframe images for different timestamps."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prompt Engineering for Sora"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Sora responds best to prompts that specify camera movement, lighting, and subject behaviour explicitly, in that order. Abstract descriptions degrade quality because the model must sample from a large distribution of valid interpretations:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Pattern: [camera] [subject + action] [environment] [style/quality]\n\n# Weak prompt — too abstract\nweak = \"A busy city\"\n\n# Strong prompt\nstrong = (\n    \"Low-angle tracking shot following a street performer juggling fire \"\n    \"on a rain-slicked Manhattan sidewalk at night, neon reflections on pavement, \"\n    \"shallow depth of field, cinematic 24mm lens\"\n)\n\n# Multi-shot: separate shots with a forward slash or scene separator\nmulti_shot = (\n    \"Wide establishing shot of a coastal lighthouse at dusk, waves crashing / \"\n    \"Cut to interior: close-up of the lighthouse keeper's weathered hands \"\n    \"adjusting a brass mechanism, warm candlelight\"\n)\n\nfor prompt, label in [(weak, \"weak\"), (strong, \"strong\"), (multi_shot, \"multi\")]:\n    print(f\"[{label}] {len(prompt.split())} words\")"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Runway Gen-3 Alpha: Professional Filmmaking Toolkit"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Runway's Gen-3 Alpha (June 2024) targets professional video production workflows. Its architecture is not publicly disclosed, but the product is positioned around "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "fine-grained directorial control"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ": explicit camera controls, per-region motion masks (Motion Brush), style consistency, and integration into existing editing pipelines."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Runway API: Text-to-Video and Image-to-Video"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# pip install runwayml\nfrom runwayml import RunwayML\nimport time, urllib.request\n\nclient = RunwayML()  # reads RUNWAYML_API_SECRET from environment\n\n# ---- Text-to-video ----\ntask = client.image_to_video.create(\n    model=\"gen3a_turbo\",          # gen3a_turbo: faster; gen3a: higher quality\n    prompt_text=(\n        \"[CINEMATIC PAN LEFT] A lone samurai stands at the edge of a cliff, \"\n        \"cherry blossoms falling in slow motion, moody overcast lighting\"\n    ),\n    # Optionally supply a conditioning image\n    # prompt_image=\"https://example.com/reference_frame.jpg\",\n    duration=10,                  # seconds (5 or 10)\n    ratio=\"1280:768\",\n    seed=2024,\n)\n\nprint(\"Task ID:\", task.id)\n\n# Poll until done (or use webhooks in production)\nwhile True:\n    task = client.tasks.retrieve(task.id)\n    if task.status in (\"SUCCEEDED\", \"FAILED\"):\n        break\n    print(f\"Status: {task.status} — waiting 5 s\")\n    time.sleep(5)\n\nif task.status == \"SUCCEEDED\":\n    video_url = task.output[0]\n    urllib.request.urlretrieve(video_url, \"runway_gen3_output.mp4\")\n    print(\"Saved runway_gen3_output.mp4\")\nelse:\n    print(\"Generation failed:\", task.failure, task.failure_code)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Director Mode: Camera Language"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Runway Gen-3 understands a cinematographic vocabulary when you embed camera direction in brackets at the start of the prompt. The model was trained on captions that use this structured format:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Camera movement tokens Runway Gen-3 responds to:\nCAMERA_TOKENS = [\n    # Translation\n    \"[DOLLY IN]\",      \"[DOLLY OUT]\",\n    \"[TRUCK LEFT]\",    \"[TRUCK RIGHT]\",\n    \"[PEDESTAL UP]\",   \"[PEDESTAL DOWN]\",\n    # Rotation\n    \"[PAN LEFT]\",      \"[PAN RIGHT]\",\n    \"[TILT UP]\",       \"[TILT DOWN]\",\n    \"[ROLL CLOCKWISE]\",\n    # Combined / cinematic\n    \"[CINEMATIC PAN LEFT]\",\n    \"[TRACKING SHOT]\",\n    \"[AERIAL SHOT]\",\n    \"[LOW ANGLE TILT UP]\",\n    \"[PUSH IN]\",       # smooth dolly in\n]\n\n# Structured prompt pattern:\n# \"[CAMERA TOKEN] Subject action. Environment. Lighting. Style.\"\nexamples = [\n    \"[DOLLY IN] A woman reads a letter by candlelight in a 19th-century library, \"\n    \"warm amber glow, dust particles floating, oil painting style\",\n\n    \"[AERIAL SHOT] Dense rainforest canopy at dawn, morning mist rising through \"\n    \"the trees, a river winding below, 8K nature documentary\",\n\n    \"[TRACKING SHOT] A cheetah at full sprint across the savannah, \"\n    \"slow-motion 120fps, golden grass blurring, high contrast wildlife photography\",\n]\n\nfor i, p in enumerate(examples):\n    print(f\"Example {i+1}: {p[:80]}...\")"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Image-to-Video with a Reference Frame"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Runway Gen-3 can animate a still image — useful for product visualisation, concept art, and character animation. The conditioning image anchors the first (or first and last) frames:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import base64\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom runwayml import RunwayML\nimport time\n\nclient = RunwayML()\n\n# Encode the conditioning image as a data URI\ndef image_to_data_uri(path: str) -> str:\n    data = Path(path).read_bytes()\n    b64  = base64.b64encode(data).decode()\n    ext  = Path(path).suffix.lstrip(\".\")\n    return f\"data:image/{ext};base64,{b64}\"\n\ntask = client.image_to_video.create(\n    model=\"gen3a_turbo\",\n    prompt_image=image_to_data_uri(\"product_photo.jpg\"),  # conditioning frame\n    prompt_text=(\n        \"[SLOW DOLLY IN] The product rotates slowly on a white pedestal, \"\n        \"soft studio lighting, reflections on glossy surface, \"\n        \"commercial photography style\"\n    ),\n    duration=5,\n    ratio=\"1280:768\",\n)\n\n# Poll for completion\nwhile True:\n    task = client.tasks.retrieve(task.id)\n    if task.status == \"SUCCEEDED\":\n        print(\"Video URL:\", task.output[0])\n        break\n    elif task.status == \"FAILED\":\n        raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed: {task.failure}\")\n    time.sleep(5)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Limitations Common to Both Models"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Text rendering"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": both models struggle to generate readable text within the video frame. Words appear plausible but contain hallucinated letterforms."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Physics edge cases"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": basic physics is convincing, but unusual interactions (objects passing through each other, inconsistent gravity) still appear. Neither model simulates physics explicitly — the behaviour is purely learned."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Hands and faces"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": fine anatomical detail — finger count, lip sync — remains challenging, especially during rapid motion."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Closed models"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": neither provides open weights or training details, making it impossible to fine-tune on custom datasets or run offline. Access depends entirely on API availability and pricing."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Content filtering"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": both apply safety classifiers that reject certain prompts, which can limit creative applications. Runway's filters are tuned for professional media; Sora's are tuned more conservatively."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
